# Cloudflare Pages isn't auto-serving 404.html for unknown routes (it returns a
# bare empty 404, so browsers show their own default error). Force the custom
# page: serve /404.html with a 404 status for anything that doesn't match a real
# static asset. Static assets — including clean URLs like /alumni — take
# precedence over _redirects rules, so real pages are unaffected; only genuinely
# unmatched paths hit this catch-all.
/*  /404.html  404
